postcontent: Custom Springfield 1911 A1 Mil Spec 45 ACP. Has the long trigger, oversized beaver tail safety, skeleton hammer, ambidextrous safety, full length guide rod, Wilson extractor & titanium firing pin, EGW O/S small radius firing pin stop (the original John Browning 1911 design, reduces recoil), and Pachmayr grips. At the time he asked me where I got it as it was the tightest fitting, slide to frame, factory 45 he'd held. Gun has never been fired without a shock buff. Comes with 7 magazines 2 OEM's, 1 GI, 2 Mecgars, and 2 Chip McCormick Shooting Star 8 round. the CMC's and the 8 round Mecgar are fitted with the new Fobus Immortal springs, OEM's and the GI are running CMC Rocket wire springs and I'll throw in some spares.
